question: Which country has launched the world’s biggest transport space ship for space station?
explanation: Japan has successfully launched an unmanned spacecraft “Kounotori8” towards the International Space Station (ISS) from the Tanegashima Space Center at Japan Aerospace Exploration Agency (JAXA) in southwestern Japan. The acronym ‘Kounotori8’ stands for “white stork\" in Japanese & intends to deliver about 5.3 tonnes of supplies to astronauts at the ISS.
